                    </table>
                    <para>Both kits are supplied with detailed installation instructions. Bearing cap cover kit part
                        number 1685190C92 for steering gears without a grease zerk fitting, will include a new bearing
                        cap cover (new seal installed) with a grease zerk fitting.
                    </para>
                    <para>Steering gears manufactured between July 1990 and January 1991 were built with an oversized
                        seal bore. Input shaft seal kit part number 1685676C92 for gears with a grease zerk fitting
                        includes a gauge/seal driver tool to measure the seal bore and install the seal in the cover.
                        The kit contains two different size metal input shaft seals; you will have to determine which
                        seal to use after measuring the bore.
                    </para>
                    <para>To make sure that the latest style kit is being used, it is identified by a
                        <emph type="bold">YELLOW</emph>
                        part number sticker. The old style kit had a
                        <emph type="bold">WHITE</emph>
                        part number sticker.
                        <emph type="bold">DO NOT USE THESE KITS</emph>. The kits with WHITE part number stickers are to
                        be returned as a complete kit to your PDC for credit. Instructions for return of parts will be
                        sent by-way-of Parts DCN message.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>REBUILD SEAL KITS</title>
                    <para>New Sheppard power steering gear rebuild seal kits are available from Service Parts. The kits
                        are listed below as kit number one and two (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="t9105013">Table 3</hotlnk>). Kit number one includes all seals needed to rebuild
                        a Sheppard M series power steering gear with a grease zerk fitting in the bearing cap cover. Kit
                        number two includes the service bearing cap cover and all the seals to rebuild a Sheppard M
                        series power steering gear without a grease zerk fitting in the bearing cap cover.
                    </para>
